content.div:
Nick Jonas may know how to succeed in business without really trying, but he’s still struggling to figure out relationships.

The 19-year-old singer/Broadway star and his girlfriend of nine months (who is also eight years his senior) have called it quits.

The pop star was dating 27-year-old Australian singer Delta Goodrem since last May, but her rep has confirmed the youngest Jonas brother (we don't count the non-famous one) is now back on the singles' market.

Goodrem's rep said on Monday in a statement, "Nick and Delta have decided mutually to end their relationship. At this point in time, they are both focused on their careers as they go on different paths. They remain friends and wish each other the best for the future."

The pair began dating shortly after Goodrem and her boyfriend of seven years, boy band singer Brian McFadden, called it quits.

It doesn't seem like Jonas is too fazed by the breakup, however. Last week, he told People magazine, "I'm enjoying love, life and friends."

Jonas, who was previously linked to Miley Cyrus, is currently living in New York City, where he’s starring in Broadway’s How to Succeed in Business Without Really Trying, replacing Darren Criss, who previously replaced Daniel Radcliffe.
